1
00:00:44,169 --> 00:00:47,380
But… what a family!

2
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,228
Mom! That's not allowed!

3
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:05,023
I'm a mother.

4
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:07,484
I can't bear to be without my youngest!

5
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:10,153
<i>I just can't stop worrying.</i>

6
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:11,404
Why? What happened?

7
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:14,449
Mom and Dad haven't even
called or texted me.

8
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:16,076
What did they tell you?

9
00:01:16,576 --> 00:01:18,328
To enjoy yourself here. Right?

10
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:22,707
Negative here, ma'am.

11
00:01:23,374 --> 00:01:24,834
What we're looking for isn't here.

12
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:40,683
Good job, everyone,
on your first day here.

13
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,060
Now, let's eat.

14
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:43,102
- All right!
- Nice!

15
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:44,729
Thank you, Lord, for this meal.

16
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,606
No dieting today!

17
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,984
Hey, buddy.

18
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:50,985
What are you calculating?

19
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:54,739
Even eating involves math?

20
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,034
Just leave him alone.

21
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,370
That's how he maintains his sexy body.

22
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:02,872
Of course he counts everything.

23
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,917
It's 20% exercise and getting sweaty.

24
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,961
And 80% is nutrition.

25
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:08,920
See?

26
00:02:09,003 --> 00:02:10,463
That's new!

27
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:12,674
We're going to eat now, okay?

28
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:14,509
- Okay, go.
- Let's go.

29
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:16,678
Wow! Sinigang in miso!

30
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:18,972
We're in for a feast!

31
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,516
Wait, where are Mom and Dad?

32
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:26,187
Tess doesn't feel like eating.

33
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:27,105
Really?

34
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:29,023
How is she feeling?

35
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,275
And why isn't Dad here either?

36
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,987
I think they just need
some time to decompress.

37
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,074
What's that?

38
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:42,495
Like unwinding, relaxing,
and relieving stress.

39
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:44,789
- Just reflecting.
- Oh, I see.

40
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:47,208
You haven't even eaten yet,
and you're already sweating.

41
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,626
True.

42
00:03:00,388 --> 00:03:01,472
Mom.

43
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:05,935
Is dinner ready?

44
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:07,437
Why are you here, sweetheart?

45
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,314
Go on, eat.

46
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:12,817
How can I eat properly
knowing you're like this, Mom?

47
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,904
They said you don't feel like eating.

48
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,616
Are you okay, Mom?

49
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:22,535
How are you feeling?

50
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:31,419
Because, sweetheart,
it's only now that it's sinking in.

51
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,714
We don't have a home anymore.

52
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:38,092
Our bakery is gone.

53
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:41,888
We have nothing to go back to.

54
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:49,479
We spent so many years
building all of that, didn't we?

55
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:55,610
You know, Mikoy,
you were still young then.

56
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,112
You were already helping me out there.

57
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,865
You and Angelito.

58
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:07,330
You both grew up in that bakery.

59
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:11,042
I guess,

60
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,129
they'll miss our cakes too, won't they?

61
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,467
You know,

62
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:23,888
it's not that I'm not grateful
that we're alive.

63
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:29,644
I'm deeply thankful to God
for keeping us safe.

64
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:37,527
But you can't expect me, son,
not to feel sad.

65
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:40,571
This is what it feels like.

66
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,616
In just one day,

67
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:48,162
everything you've worked so hard for,

68
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,958
every dream you've built,

69
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,004
can just disappear, son.

70
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,965
It feels so unfair, doesn't it?

71
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:24,490
Are you okay, Angelito?

72
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:27,744
I'm okay.

73
00:05:28,786 --> 00:05:33,041
It's just that I still haven't
talked to Mom and Dad.

74
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:38,838
But maybe they're just busy.

75
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:41,966
They probably have a lot going on.

76
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:47,805
Knowing your parents,
that's exactly what they'd say.

77
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:52,185
But you know,
I've never seen you like this before.

78
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,062
You're so anxious.

79
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:55,563
I'm not used to it.

80
00:05:56,230 --> 00:06:02,236
But maybe your worries are justified.

81
00:06:05,865 --> 00:06:08,409
You're right, Mom. It does feel unfair.

82
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:11,996
We're the ones who work hard every day.

83
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,416
We're the ones trying to earn
an honest living, and yet…

84
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:18,211
we're the ones going through this.

85
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,257
I'm sorry, Mom.

86
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:26,052
Son.

87
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:28,763
None of this is your fault.

88
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,438
Wait, where are you going?

89
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:42,318
I'll go first.

90
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:48,032
Come on, come on.

91
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:01,879
Wait, wait.

92
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,215
Can you believe this?

93
00:07:04,298 --> 00:07:05,800
There, now we have some light.

94
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:08,886
Can you believe this?

95
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:12,056
We actually have to climb up here
just to get a signal.

96
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,059
How did you manage that?

97
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,562
Who do you think I am?

98
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:19,480
That's easy for me.

99
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:24,277
Let's see if there's a signal.

100
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:27,655
Up here.

101
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:30,825
Wait, I thought this was
a signal spot. How come…

102
00:07:31,325 --> 00:07:32,368
it's still gone?

103
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,828
Still nothing.

104
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,919
- Okay.
- You're too impatient.

105
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,630
Let's just have faith, Mom.

106
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:49,469
We'll defeat those crime syndicates.

107
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:52,722
Especially La Morte Bianca.

108
00:07:54,932 --> 00:07:57,602
Because we're fighting together.

109
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:00,521
We'll get through this.

110
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,816
- Thank you.
- Once all of this is over,

111
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:07,195
Mom, I promise,

112
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,989
we'll make your dreams come true next.

113
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:12,158
Okay?

114
00:08:12,658 --> 00:08:14,452
Thank you, son.

115
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:28,090
There it is.

116
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:37,141
There!

117
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:40,436
TEMPORARY CLOSED
PINAGPALA SPECIAL BAKESHOP

118
00:08:41,103 --> 00:08:42,063
Me too.

119
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,774
Still nothing here.

120
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:54,659
Angelito.

121
00:08:57,328 --> 00:09:03,584
Didn't you tell me that
your parents were just busy?

122
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:04,919
Yes.

123
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:11,884
And you also said
they had a lot to take care of.

124
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,010
Yes.

125
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:20,184
What do you think they've been busy with?

126
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:23,437
Aside from running the bakery?

127
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:26,607
What do you mean?

128
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:29,110
Well…

129
00:09:29,193 --> 00:09:30,319
Oh, no.

130
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:33,614
I checked your family's Fishbook page,

131
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:36,075
and there are so many comments.

132
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,244
Here's the first one.

133
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:39,745
Listen carefully.

134
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:42,707
It says, "So that was my last cake.

135
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,709
I should've ordered more."

136
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,170
Here's another one.

137
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:52,133
"Stay strong. God bless."

138
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:53,801
See?

139
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:55,511
Here's another.

140
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:59,223
It says, "We'll miss your cakes.

141
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,309
Please stay safe."

142
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,644
- What…
- There are so many!

143
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:07,398
"Whoever did this should pay."

144
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:08,566
"Justice."

145
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,360
- Justice?
- Justice?

146
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,864
What do you think happened?

147
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:17,491
That's exactly what we need to find out.

148
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,626
What's wrong, Mom?

149
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:29,879
Why do you still look so stressed?

150
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:35,468
Because your father is so stubborn.

151
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:37,053
Why?

152
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:45,519
Dad left?

153
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,231
Where did he go?

154
00:10:56,030 --> 00:11:00,409
<i>Tess, Mikoy, I'm sorry</i>
<i>I couldn't say goodbye.</i>

155
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:06,916
<i>Nothing is more important</i>
<i>than making sure we finish this mission,</i>

156
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:09,251
<i>safe and together.</i>

157
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:13,130
<i>Don't worry anymore about how I escaped.</i>

158
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:15,508
<i>Don't even picture it.</i>

159
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,343
<i>What you should focus on</i>

160
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:20,805
<i>is the safety of everyone</i>
<i>in the safe house.</i>

161
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:22,890
<i>Mikoy.</i>

162
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,935
<i>Back when our house</i>
<i>was under surveillance,</i>

163
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:30,773
<i>your friends volunteered</i>
<i>to watch over our home.</i>

164
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:33,317
<i>They patrolled day and night.</i>

165
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,863
<i>Now it's only right</i>
<i>that we return the favor.</i>

166
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:39,990
<i>They're family now.</i>

167
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:42,118
Yes, Dad!

168
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,953
I'll take care of the guys.

169
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:50,584
<i>Please bear with their antics for now.</i>

170
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:54,171
<i>Tess, my love.</i>

171
00:11:55,589 --> 00:12:00,970
<i>I understand how devastating</i>
<i>all of this has been.</i>

172
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:07,351
<i>It wasn't just our home or our bakery</i>
<i>that was destroyed.</i>

173
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:11,856
<i>Countless memories and dreams</i>
<i>we built there too.</i>

174
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,484
<i>I'm hurting too.</i>

175
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,361
<i>It's okay, my love.</i>

176
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:20,448
<i>And since your tears just won't stop…</i>

177
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:27,455
<i>don't forget to drink plenty of water.</i>

178
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,665
<i>You need to stay hydrated.</i>

179
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:35,337
<i>Despite everything,</i>
<i>we have to keep moving.</i>

180
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,466
<i>While I take care of things for all of us,</i>

181
00:12:39,091 --> 00:12:42,011
<i>promise me you'll look after each other.</i>

182
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:44,180
<i>I love you all so much.</i>

183
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:46,682
<i>And I promise the day is near</i>
<i>when the four of us</i>

184
00:12:46,765 --> 00:12:50,019
<i>will be together again, with Angelito.</i>

185
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,104
<i>For now, all I ask</i>

186
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:54,940
<i>is that you trust one another.</i>

187
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:59,069
<i>Because those who love also trust.</i>

188
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:01,197
<i>The one who loves,</i>

189
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:03,449
<i>Mario.</i>

190
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:22,635
I have an idea.

191
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,470
How about this?

192
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,972
I'll report to Daddy Sir.

193
00:13:28,516 --> 00:13:29,767
There we go!

194
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:36,440
‪NORBERTO S. RUIZ
‪GENERAL

195
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:37,608
Sofie.

196
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,652
You called. Is it an emergency?

197
00:13:39,735 --> 00:13:41,111
Why?

198
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:43,280
Am I bothering you?

199
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:46,700
Don't tell me you're on a date.

200
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:47,743
Admit it.

201
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:50,829
You think I still have time to date?

202
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:53,958
Okay, let's skip the small talk.

203
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:56,752
Why did you call?

204
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:01,674
But I hope you'll be honest with me too.

205
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:05,261
<i>Daddy Sir, what's happening</i>
<i>to the Pinagpalas?</i>

206
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:08,806
Why is their bakery temporarily closed?

207
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:10,099
Are they okay?

208
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:18,023
Yes, I'm listening.

209
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,526
It's just so strange, Daddy Sir.

210
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,987
I saw something on Fishbook.

211
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,573
There were so many comments,
like something terrible happened.

212
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:30,077
They were saying someone
needs to be held accountable.

213
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,371
What happened?

214
00:14:32,454 --> 00:14:37,835
Sofie, didn't I tell you before
not to interfere in other people's lives?

215
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:41,463
Maybe they're going through something.

216
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:47,052
Daddy Sir, they're like family to me.

217
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:50,306
I think my concern is valid, isn't it?

218
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:56,061
And I'm asking you
because maybe you have an…

219
00:14:58,022 --> 00:15:00,316
Maybe you know something
about what they're going through.

220
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:05,195
Sofie, didn't I also tell you that my work

221
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:09,283
requires the utmost confidentiality?

222
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:14,330
I understand that, Daddy Sir,
and I understand you too.

223
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,373
Especially when you're hiding something.

224
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:21,837
Come on, Sofie. This conversation
isn't going anywhere.

225
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,839
<i>Okay, I'm busy at the office.</i>

226
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,424
We'll talk another time, when…

227
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:29,386
when it's no longer another family
you want to know about. Okay?

228
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:31,972
Wait, Daddy Sir! Daddy Sir!

229
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:35,017
What did he say?

230
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:40,940
You know, Angelito, I smell something.

231
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:53,953
Do not divulge any information to Sofie.

232
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,121
I know my daughter.

233
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:02,920
She won't stop until she gets answers,
and she won't stop bothering you either.

234
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:04,755
- We'll handle it, sir.
- Copy, sir.

235
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:08,717
NORBERTO S. RUIZ
GENERAL

236
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:11,428
What's that?

237
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,516
Move!

238
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:18,477
- What's going on?!
- Get down!

239
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,020
- Come on.
- What's happening?

240
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:21,188
- Why's the alarm going off?
- Mikoy, hide!

241
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:22,564
- Mikoy, hide!
- Why?

242
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,358
- Why? What's happening?
- Take cover!

243
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:27,319
Mikoy, what are you doing?

244
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:29,113
Mikoy, what you're doing is dangerous!

245
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:30,864
Can you just wait a second?

246
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,200
Lower your guns first!

247
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:35,744
I really think that's Chiara. Okay?

248
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:37,663
She doesn't even have a phone.

249
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:39,081
So how else could she contact us?

250
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:41,583
Trust me.

251
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,003
I'm absolutely sure it's Chiara!

252
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:46,964
Mikoy, even if it is Chiara,
we need to be more careful.

253
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:48,465
She's still La Fornarina.

254
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,092
Exactly, Agent Alex.

255
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,343
What if it really is Chiara?

256
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,514
Even Cocoy believes me.

257
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:58,434
So please, lower your guns.

258
00:16:59,018 --> 00:16:59,977
What now, Bok?

259
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:12,865
I told you!

260
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:20,748
But why are you pointing guns?

261
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:23,876
Is this how you welcome someone home now?

262
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:26,962
It's not like I was gone that long.

263
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:30,132
You know… Preventive measures.

264
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:40,976
To keep you from running away again.

265
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:11,548
Come on, sweetheart. Have a bite first.

266
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:16,220
Is it good? Want some dipping sauce?

267
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:17,971
Extra chili and calamansi?

268
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:20,182
This is enough, sweetheart.

269
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:21,225
Go on, eat.

270
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:22,476
Have a drink first.

271
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,020
It has lots of ice and a slice of lemon.

272
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:26,563
All good now?

273
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:29,608
Wow, you're so slim,
but you can really eat!

274
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,861
She can easily finish
a whole mound of rice.

275
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,238
What about the rest of us?

276
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:35,864
Oh, come on.

277
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:39,243
Even if the three of us teamed up,
she could still take us down.

278
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:41,537
Oh, stop it!

279
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:45,040
Chiara, I'm so glad you're back.

280
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,792
How are your mom and dad?

281
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,711
I only got to talk to my dad.

282
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:53,048
It was only for a short while
because the area was well secured.

283
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,134
My sweetheart is really amazing.

284
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:58,387
You know, sweetheart,
I could just be a house husband.

285
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:01,056
After your long day, when you come home,

286
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,057
there'll be food ready for you.

287
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:04,518
Then after your shower,
I can give you a massage.

288
00:19:04,601 --> 00:19:06,061
So you can relax.

289
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,688
What do you think? Sound good?

290
00:19:08,188 --> 00:19:12,192
I can't tell if you're being romantic
or just planning way ahead.

291
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:15,487
But sweetheart,
before you become a house husband,

292
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,531
let me finish eating first.

293
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:19,533
- This is my first meal today.
- Right, sorry!

294
00:19:19,616 --> 00:19:20,909
Here, keep eating.

295
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:24,788
I think she's harmless.

296
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:32,129
What information did Chiara get
after talking to Viktor?

297
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:36,592
And what information did she give Viktor?

298
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,054
Add some soup.

299
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:43,473
Yes. This has some soup. Of course.

300
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,272
More.

301
00:19:58,989 --> 00:20:00,282
Chiara has returned.

302
00:20:02,492 --> 00:20:05,871
But of course, she'll need
a full briefing early tomorrow morning.

303
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:10,584
And Chiara needs to be
interrogated immediately.

304
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:22,137
Following our protocols upon your return,
we need to observe you first.

305
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,724
We need to make sure you're safe

306
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:28,602
and that you won't compromise
everyone else's safety here.

307
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,942
You know…

308
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,861
You're just wasting your time
with all these protocols.

309
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:41,740
Instead of taking action
against La Morte Bianca,

310
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:44,326
here we are, listening to your policies.

311
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,579
Just relax.

312
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:48,538
Relax?

313
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:53,835
Want me to get handcuffed too?

314
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,212
So we can match?

315
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:58,674
Agent Alex, Agent Sianong,
maybe you should handcuff me too.

316
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:00,175
I feel bad for my sweetheart.

317
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,551
Sure.

318
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:03,595
If that's what he wants.

319
00:21:07,307 --> 00:21:09,851
You don't really have
a choice in this situation.

320
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,024
Are you punishing me?

321
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:17,859
You could say that.

322
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,241
But what about Mikoy?

323
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:27,160
Does he get a free pass
because he's your friend?

324
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:36,795
Those are orders from headquarters.

325
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:40,382
You just got back,

326
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:43,552
and we have to make sure
you don't put us at risk.

327
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:49,349
Agent Sianong, Agent Alex,
maybe you can give Chiara a chance?

328
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:57,357
Chiara can't be allowed to run away again,

329
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:59,985
and you can't keep going along
with her plans.

330
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:04,656
I thought this was
a national security issue.

331
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,036
Not keep relying on the same old methods.

332
00:22:09,911 --> 00:22:12,247
Do you even realize
that because you two escaped,

333
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:14,708
we were inches away from being fired?

334
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:49,201
And it's true

335
00:22:49,284 --> 00:22:52,204
that you're the one who ordered
that I be separated from everyone,

336
00:22:52,287 --> 00:22:53,872
for observation.

337
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:11,431
Don't tell me you called just to complain.

338
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:24,069
Meaning, sooner or later, we're all dead.

339
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:21,728
And to counter that plan,
we need a team focused solely on her.

340
00:25:25,065 --> 00:25:26,733
GENERAL NORBERTO

341
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:31,154
What information you have?

342
00:25:31,238 --> 00:25:35,033
This La Morte Bianca
blew up the Pinagpala's bakery.

343
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:36,576
<i>Even their house, burned to ashes.</i>

344
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,620
How's our in laws?

345
00:25:38,703 --> 00:25:41,039
<i>They were fortunate to escape</i>
<i>right before the explosions.</i>

346
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:49,047
Agent Sianong, hello.

347
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:52,759
Aunt Tess, I want to ask something.

348
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:56,680
Where is Mario?
We haven't seen him since last night.

349
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:03,061
<i>Chiara, I can't afford</i>
<i>to lose this immunity.</i>

350
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:05,397
Most importantly now that
my family is involved.

351
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,190
And now that our house is gone.

352
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:09,359
As well as our bakery.

353
00:26:09,442 --> 00:26:11,820
This immunity is the only thing
I can rely on.

354
00:26:12,946 --> 00:26:13,989
So please…

355
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,116
Can't you rely on me instead?
